RUN: %COMPILE %S/main.st && %RUN | %CHECK %s

Verify that an {external} FB with a constant array initializer works in a
split-compilation scenario:
  1. fb_body.c provides the FB body (compiled to .o by lit.local.cfg)
  2. --constructors-only generates the ctor object (with memcpy from .const_init)
  3. main.st links both and accesses the initialized array

CHECK: 10
CHECK: 30
CHECK: 50
CHECK: 99
